 148:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 149:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****     *** Callback registration ***
 150:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****     =============================================
 151:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****     [..]
 152:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       The compilation define  USE_HAL_DAC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 153:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 154:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 155:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****     Use Functions HAL_DAC_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback,
 156:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       it allows to register following callbacks:
 157:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvCpltCallbackCh1     : callback when a half transfer is completed on Ch1.
 158:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvHalfCpltCallbackCh1 : callback when a transfer is completed on Ch1.
 159:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ErrorCallbackCh1        : callback when an error occurs on Ch1.
 160:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) DMAUnderrunCallbackCh1  : callback when an underrun error occurs on Ch1.
 161:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvCpltCallbackCh2     : callback when a half transfer is completed on Ch2.
 162:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvHalfCpltCallbackCh2 : callback when a transfer is completed on Ch2.
 163:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ErrorCallbackCh2        : callback when an error occurs on Ch2.
 164:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) DMAUnderrunCallbackCh2  : callback when an underrun error occurs on Ch2.
 165:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) MspInitCallback         : DAC MspInit.
 166:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) MspDeInitCallback       : DAC MspdeInit.
 167:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 168:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       and a pointer to the user callback function.
 169:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 170:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****     Use function HAL_DAC_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 171:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       weak (surcharged) function. It allows to reset following callbacks:
 172:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvCpltCallbackCh1     : callback when a half transfer is completed on Ch1.
 173:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvHalfCpltCallbackCh1 : callback when a transfer is completed on Ch1.
 174:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ErrorCallbackCh1        : callback when an error occurs on Ch1.
 175:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) DMAUnderrunCallbackCh1  : callback when an underrun error occurs on Ch1.
 176:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvCpltCallbackCh2     : callback when a half transfer is completed on Ch2.
 177:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ConvHalfCpltCallbackCh2 : callback when a transfer is completed on Ch2.
 178:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) ErrorCallbackCh2        : callback when an error occurs on Ch2.
 179:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) DMAUnderrunCallbackCh2  : callback when an underrun error occurs on Ch2.
 180:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) MspInitCallback         : DAC MspInit.
 181:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) MspDeInitCallback       : DAC MspdeInit.
 182:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       (+) All Callbacks
 183:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       This function) takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle and the Callback ID.
 184:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 185:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       By default, after the HAL_DAC_Init and if the state is HAL_DAC_STATE_RESET
 186:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak (surcharged) functions.
 187:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
 188:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       reset to the legacy weak (surcharged) functions in the HAL_DAC_Init
 189:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       and  HAL_DAC_DeInit only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 190:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_DAC_Init and HAL_DAC_DeInit
 191:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 192:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
 193:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
 194:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
 195:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 196:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       during the Init/DeInit.
 197:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 198:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       using HAL_DAC_RegisterCallback before calling HAL_DAC_DeInit
 199:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c ****       or HAL_DAC_Init function.
 200:Drivers/STM32F4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32f4xx_hal_dac.c **** 
